    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Male Accomplishments</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ronald Halweil letter comments on David Dill's August 16 letter on male intellectual accomplishments (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>To David Dill's short list of male accomplishments (''Those Extra Male Neurons Have Accomplished Quite a Lot,'' letter, Aug. 16), I would add nuclear weapons, total warfare and genocide. Whenever women have had the same opportunities as men, they have excelled in all endeavors.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>To David Dill's short list of male accomplishments (''Those Extra Male Neurons Have Accomplished Quite a Lot,'' letter, Aug. 16), I would add nuclear weapons, total warfare and genocide. Whenever women have had the same opportunities as men, they have excelled in all endeavors.</p>
        <p>By the way, who raises, nurtures and encourages all the accomplished men?</p>
        <p>RONALD HALWEIL  Bayonne, N.J., Aug. 16, 1997</p>
      </block>
